{% if "orm_injection" in data.contains_type %}
    <li>{% trans %}We identified that the following URLs are vulnerable to ORM injection:{% endtrans %}
        <ul>
            {% for report in data.reports %}
                {% if report.report_type == "orm_injection" %}
                    {% for message in report.additional_data.result %}
                        <li>
                            {{ message.url }}
                            {% if message.code == report.additional_data.statements.orm_injection %}
                                :
                                {% trans trimmed %}
                                    ORM injection: user input is being passed directly to ORM query methods,
                                    allowing an attacker to manipulate query logic by appending ORM-specific
                                    suffixes (e.g. __startswith, __contains, __gt) to parameter names. This
                                    can be used to extract sensitive data from the database by brute-forcing
                                    field values character by character.
                                {% endtrans %}
                            {% elif message.code == report.additional_data.statements.orm_sensitive_field_access %}
                                :
                                {% trans trimmed %}
                                    ORM sensitive field access: the endpoint allows filtering on sensitive fields
                                    (such as password hashes, admin flags, or email addresses) through ORM lookup
                                    parameters. An attacker can use this to enumerate users, extract password hashes,
                                    or identify privileged accounts.
                                {% endtrans %}
                            {% endif %}
                        </li>
                    {% endfor %}
                {% endif %}
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p>
            {% trans trimmed %}
                ORM injection occurs when user input is passed directly to ORM query methods
                (e.g. Model.objects.filter(**request.GET) in Django). Even though no raw SQL is written,
                an attacker can manipulate the query logic to access data they should not be able to see.
                To fix this, validate and whitelist allowed parameter names before passing them to the ORM.
            {% endtrans %}
        </p>
{% endif %}
